<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,996,1562]" box="[151,952,996,1022]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[151,235,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female</emphasis>
. Seventh sternite posterior margin convex medially (
<figureCitation box="[829,938,996,1022]" captionStart="FIGURES 10" captionStartId="45.[151,264,1908,1933]" captionTargetBox="[228,1374,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure@45.[197,1391,166,1888]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="FIGURES 10 A–L. Female sternite VII of Coelidiini. A. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.; B. C. ostenta (Distant); C. C. kodikanelensis Nielson; D. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao). E. Olidiana brevis (Walker); F. O. kirkaldyi (Nielson); G. O. umroensis sp. nov.; H. Singillatus serratispatulatus sp. nov.; I. Trinoridia dialata sp. nov.; J. T. piperica sp. nov.; K. T. ramamurthyi sp. nov.; L. Webbolidia andamana sp. nov.; L." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366564/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 10 B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,996,1562]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis box="[199,390,1032,1058]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Female genitalia</emphasis>
. Valvula I, in lateral view with dorsal sculptured area and ventral sculptured area restricted to apical 1/5 (
<figureCitation box="[275,364,1068,1094]" captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[187,1369,186,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 11 A–P. Female valvulae I and II. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.: A &amp; B. Valvula I; C &amp; D. Valvula II. C. ostenta (Distant): E&amp; F. Valvula I; G &amp; H. Valvula II. C. kodikanelensis Nielson: I &amp; J. Valvula I; K &amp; L. Valvula II. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao): M &amp; N. Valvula I; O &amp; P. Valvula II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366566/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
E–F). Valvula II in lateral view, sinuate with dentation restricted to apical 1/3, each tooth widely separated, regualraly triangular (
<figureCitation box="[516,606,1104,1130]" captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="46.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[187,1369,186,1891]" captionTargetId="figure@46.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="46" captionText="FIGURES 11 A–P. Female valvulae I and II. Calodia neofusca sp. nov.: A &amp; B. Valvula I; C &amp; D. Valvula II. C. ostenta (Distant): E&amp; F. Valvula I; G &amp; H. Valvula II. C. kodikanelensis Nielson: I &amp; J. Valvula I; K &amp; L. Valvula II. Glaberana khasiensis (Rao): M &amp; N. Valvula I; O &amp; P. Valvula II." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366566/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
G–H).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,996,1562]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
